Does MAC have the concept of XDG_RUNTIME_DIR, or any runtime dir at all?
Pointing it at ~/.docker/config.json might be the best we can do.  Although ~/.containers/config.json would be my preferred root.

@Sher-Chowdhury WDYT?

@rhatdan Very sorry for the late response. 

I tried the authfile appraoch but it didn't seem to work:

```
$ cat ~/tmp/docker-config.json
{
  "auths": {
    "exampleregistry.com": {
      "username": "iamapikey",
      "password": "xxxxxx",
      "email": "a@b.c",
      "auth": "xxxxxxxxxxx"
    }
  }
}
$ skopeo login exampleregistry.com --authfile ~/tmp/docker-config.json
Authenticating with existing credentials...
Existing credentials are invalid, please enter valid username and password
Username (iamapikey): iamapikey
Password:      (had to copy and paste here)
Login Succeeded!
```

I had copy+plus paste the password to successfully login. At least it did seem to read the config file to set the default username, which in this example was 'iamapikey'.
